> Looking for a super quick and tasty midweek dinner option? Try cooking up our
> Ginger Hoisin Pork Udon in just 15 minutes for a delicious and speedy meal.

Heat a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}.
Break up the mince as it cooks. IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after
handling raw mince. Cook so there's no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @Garlic Cloves{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).
Drain the fat from the pork. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.
Add the @Coleslaw Mix{120%grams} and @Sugar Snap Peas{80%grams} to the pork.
Fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.
Stir in the @Ginger Puree{15%grams} and garlic. Fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @Hoisin Sauce{60%grams}, @Soy Sauce{25%ml} and @Water{50%ml} (see
pantry).
Bring to the boil and simmer, ~{1-2%minutes}.
Add the @Udon Noodles{220%grams} to the pan. Toss to coat, using a #fork{} to
gently separate them.
Simmer until piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season if needed. Add a splash of water if it's too thick.
Share the noodles between your #bowls{}.
Enjoy!